# User Guide for MarconiBB
##### Created By: Marcon D. - Strambini E. - Tezza G.

# Introduction
The purpose of our project is to ease the booking of rooms and laboratories inside the institute, while speeding up the process and save paper.
We use an all-in-one solution, based on a microcomputer that serves as a terminal where the end users can book room. The software is easy to use, fast to learn, with a minimal and eye catching interface.

# Getting started
The application is based on a physical terminal used to navigate menus. It consists of coloured buttons, corresponding to executable actions presented each time on screen.

# Hompage
![Home page screenshot](data:image/png;base64,)
To start using the application just swipe the internal badge on the terminal reader.
If the reading was successful your username will be displayed on screen.

![User List screenshot](data:image/png;base64,)
At this step you can swipe different badges, one for each person taking part in the booking.
As soon as the user is satisfied with the entry, he can proceed to the next step by interacting with the terminal using the appropriate button corresponding to the indication at the bottom of the screen.
He can then proceed with the booking or cancel the operation.

# Time selection
![Date selection screenshot](data:image/png;base64,)
At this point, to complete the reservation, you must select a day from the proposed list. The choice can be made between today and the following seven days, using the corresponding button as indicated at the bottom of the screen, scrolling through the options.
As soon as the user is satisfied with the entry, he can proceed to the next step by interacting with the terminal using the appropriate button corresponding to the indication at the bottom of the screen.

![Hour selection screenshot](data:image/png;base64,)
Select now the booking time interval you wish to reserve.
As soon as the user is satisfied with the entry, he can proceed to the next step by interacting with the terminal using the appropriate button corresponding to the indication at the bottom of the screen.

# Room type selection
![Room type selection screenshot](data:image/png;base64,)
At this point it will be possible to select whether you want to book a classical classroom or a laboratory in a similar way to previously used ones.
As soon as the user is satisfied with the entry, he can proceed to the next step by interacting with the terminal using the appropriate button corresponding to the indication at the bottom of the screen.

# Checkout page
![Checkout page selection](data:image/png;base64,)
When the operation is completed a recap page will be shown to check the data entered and confirm or cancel the entire booking.
For the last time proceed to by interacting with the terminal using the appropriate button corresponding to the indication at the bottom of the screen.
